Description: The sunflower designed with darker brown circular disc,which featues orange stitching grid. It is surrounded by the two thick layer of yellow petals.

The design features a symmetrical flower shape constructed from several layer of petalas. The outer layer has white pointed petals. The interior layer consist of smaller pointed petals in two shade of purple. At the center of flower it has the small, solid, round felt ball in lighter purple acting as a pistil.
The succulent plants has sits on the tiny pots. The plant featues soft, woolen green leaves with small pot .
The stem features a long,upright spikes.The color gradient on spike starts with a deep, vivid purple at bottom, transitioning through lighter shades of purple toward the middle and white on the top.

The design featues a flower head and small part of the stem. The tulip bloom is a single piece of thick cut into a classic, rounded shape with three distinct pointed lobes at the top colored in pink. It is connected to a small rectangular section of green stem.

The cactus is made of dark green felt and features three distinct arms branching upwards from the base. White stitching felt spots are evenly distributed across the surface, representing the cactus spines. Each arm is topped with a small, brightly colored felt flower: purple, yellow, and blue. The cactus is planted in a pot made of soft, round felt balls and various small grey and white felt stones.
The smooth solid felt ball that form the nut, conical top. It has the light tan on the bottom and dark brown on the top and stem.

Flower is created using individual felted wool balls. The center of each bloom is a single, larger felt ball in soft pink. Surrounding the center is a ring of uniform, smaller white felt balls that form the petals. It has a thin, flexible, dark green felt-covered stem.

Flower is created from cut felt pieces. It petals featues a pointed crisp with the rounded felt on the middle. The flower are attached to thin, flexible, dark green felt stem and separate piece of long folded dark green leaf.
The flower is designed with six rounded felt balls forming the petals centered around a smaller felt ball acts as pistil. The bloom is attached to a long, thin stem covered in light green felt.

The flower spikes is densely constructed from individual pieces of vibrant purple felt. At the base of the flower head , a small piece of dark green felt is attached to represent the leaves. The bloom connect to thin, flexibile dark green felt wrapped stem.
The flower is composed of layers of soft pointed felt petals. The bloom is connected to a long , thin, flexible stem covered in the dark green felt.

The flower head is vibrant pink or purple with small yellow center. The bloom is connected to a long, thin, flexible stem covered in the dark green felt. Midway down the stem,two small, small folded pieces of dark green felt leaves are attached.
The flower head is crated from numerous layers of cut felt pointed edges. It is connected with a thin, long, flexible stem covered in dark green felt.
The simple rounded felt ball bud on the middle is connected to a thin, long, flexible stem covered in lime green felt. It has partial encased by the pointed green leaves.

The flower head is dense and features multiple layers of small, tightly clustered petal, vibrant red felt. The bloom is cradled by dark green felt at the base and is attached to a long, thin, flexible stem covered in dark green felt. A small, pointed felt leaf protrudes from the stem midway down.

The design features four individual clusters of stylized, cupped flowers, evenly spaced along the upper section of the stem, all made from a soft purplefelt. These flower clusters are attached  to a long, thin, flexible stem covered in dark green felt.

The bloom is made from soft felt formed slightly opened tulip cup shape in a gentle color. It is attached to a long, thin, flexible stem covered in dark green felt. A prominent feature is the single, large, folded felt leaf that wraps around the stem, also in dark green.

The flower spike is densely constructed from numerous small  layered pieces of  yellow forming a textured, cylindrical head. At the base of the bloom, two small, pointed pieces of dark green felt represent the leaves . The flower head is attached to a long, thin stem covered in dark green felt.

The design features a stylized sunflower head with bright golden yellow felt petals surrounding a dense, circular black felt center. The flower is attached to a flexible stem covered in dark green felt, which also includes a small felt leaf detail.
The bloom is composed of felted wool balls, a central large ball surrounded by the smaller balls that act as petal. The flower head is attached to a thin, flelxible stem covered in dark green felt.

The flower is made with multiple soft layer of swirling petals that represent the roses. On the middles of the roses the tiny white balls on the thin stem acts as gypsy. All the roses are attached to thin, flexible dark green felt .
